Solve The contents of chal.py tell us that the flag has been xored with a key and we only have the resulting encrypted flag.
#! /usr/bin/env python flag = &#34;XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX&#34; enc_flag = [91,241,101,166,85,192,87,188,110,164,99,152,98,252,34,152,117,164,99,162,107] key = [0, 0, 0, 0] KEY_LEN = 4 # Encrypt the flag for idx, c in enumerate(flag): enc_flag = ord(c) ^ key[idx % len(key)] The xor operation has properties that make it simple to reverse.
